text:
175 E. Broadway, (The Jewish Daily Forward Building), south side, between Rutgers and Jefferson Streets, (panoramic view eastward towards the East River and Corlears Hook).

Corlears Hook is the land protuberance this side of the Williamsburg Bridge where the river bends to turn northward. Henry Street is the thoroughfare in the center of View 1. The smokestacks on the Brooklyn Shore in View 2 are at the U. S. Navy Yard.

February 14, 1930
Views: 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr
title: General view - East Broadway - East.
